[h3 id=Introduction 
	[b 
		"Introduction
	]b
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Imagine: Movie Star
	]em
	" is touch-screen 
	[em 
		"Guitar Hero
	]em
	" for teenage girls, released for the Nintendo DS near the tail-end of 2008 by 
	[em 
		"Ubisoft
	]em
	" and developed by 
	[em 
		"Powerhead Games
	]em
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Yep, not really gonna bother with a more formal description for this game, seeing as how it’s April Fools' Day and I made this TAS with the intention of it being rejected.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Objective 
	[b 
		"Objective
	]b
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"This movie plays through all of the songs and dress-up activities on Hard difficulty, which is unlocked by first beating the game on Normal, aiming for the highest possible score one can get in each level.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Each level has a maximum amount of 1000 fans. Last time I sat down to play this game casually, the game was pretty lenient with how many notes I was allowed to miss, so even if you’re not on an FC run, you can still gain 1000 fans per song quite easily, even on Hard. Every criteria you can check off in the dress-up levels nets you 50 points and 250 fans each.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The stars in the upper-left that you can use by touching them or using the D-Pad cut the amount of points you get in half when they’re active, so I avoid using them for the whole movie.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=BrokenNotes 
	[b 
		"Broken Notes
	]b
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Broken notes are a very rare sight in rhythm games, with their documentation being fairly scarce. Unfortunately, some charts in 
	[em 
		"Imagine: Movie Star
	]em
	" weren’t playtested as well as others.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Premiere Night
	]em
	" and 
	[em 
		"The Grand Opening
	]em
	" both have sphere-catching sections where there’s a significant lull of spheres near the end, which forces the game to break your note streak numerous times.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"The Chase Scene
	]em
	" and 
	[em 
		"Run For The Hills
	]em
	"' first sphere-catching sections are only slightly broken: There’s a few spheres that can’t be caught near the start, but you can very briefly let go of the touch screen to bank in the first couple of spheres that can be caught. At least your note streak can’t be forced broken to these parts.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"True Confessions
	]em
	" has a yellow note immediately after its sphere-catching section, which you can only hit with a “Good” or just outright miss it because the transition back to tapping the notes takes too long to hit it with a “Perfect” and keep the note streak going. Funnily enough, getting “Good” on a sustain doesn’t break your note streak.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=PossibleImprovements 
	[b 
		"Possible Improvements
	]b
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"I don’t know... make a bot, perhaps? Either way, it’s pretty much impossible to hit those aforementioned broken notes any better/at all.
	$LF
]div
